@@ -282,3 +282,4 @@
 - Tightened Document2 O1 runtime contracts for the remote smoke path by moving ReAct final-payload adapters out of the harness, making resolver/detail prompts emit complete canonical documents, disabling O1 patch write permissions in detail/resolver nodes, adding single-step resolver runtime budgets, and recording serial-agent timeout checkpoints.
 - Corrected Document2 prompt and ReAct output-contract examples so `ExpectationUnitDocument.realized_facts` strictly match the current `RealizedFact` Pydantic model, omitting unsupported `event_time` fields and treating `certainty` as plain short text.
 - Aligned Document2 orchestration after the candidate-contract audit by limiting detail generation to candidate acceptance, bridging blocking review findings into resolver-visible objections, revalidating deterministic blockers after transactions, keeping promotion read-only, allowing one-to-three construction shells, and rejecting list-wrapped resolver candidates.
+- Raised the Document2 O1 resolver workflow timeout to 240 seconds, added resolver input-context size telemetry to serial dispatch checkpoints, and grouped objection-resolution batches by semantic root cause to reduce repeated blocker fan-in during smoke runs.
